  %h1
    Sinatra - Deck.js Song
  %p
    A suggestion from @vzmind
%section.slide
  %h2 How to host your own slide manager 
  %ol
    %li
      %h3 Copy that Github repo
      %p git clone git@github.com:vzmind/personal-deckjs.git
    %li
      %h3 Deploy it on heroku
      %p you know the usual git push heroku :)
%section.slide
  %h2 How to add slides
  %ol
    %li
      %h3 Simply add a new listner to deck-song.rb 
      %pre
        %code
          get "/my-new_song"
          haml :my_new_song
    %li
      %h3 Create a file my_new_song.haml in views
      %p You can start editing your slideshow
%section.slide
  %h2 Customize your slideshow
  %ol
    %li
      %h3 A section tag is a slide
      %p Just add as much as you want.
    %li
      %h3 Customize the introduction.css if needed
      %p It's already coming with a basic shadowing style.
    %li
      %h3 If you are more advanced
      %p change the transition js file
    %li
      %h3 Choose Themes
      %p Try to pick an other theme from the deck.js folder

